race.comment: ALL TOO MYSTI (2) was strong first-up in town when claimed late. Not as effective last time but drops slightly in grade and keeps Toeroek aboard. Needs luck from the wide alley but if the gaps appear she'll take plenty of stopping. ONE MORE SONG (4) returned with a bang at Murray Bridge, putting 4L on her nearest rival to shed the maiden tag. Has come back in terrific order and can keep the momentum rolling with Pannell sticking from the gun draw. TRANTORO (7) was below her best in town last time, finishing over 2L behind ALL TOO MYSTI and MEG'S MAGIC. Freshened with 38 days and can give this a shake if back to her best. THE PLASTICS (3) resumes from a short break and has won fresh before. Trialled sharply in readiness and can make her presence felt. MEG'S MAGIC (10) has struggled to fire of late but has genuine claims on best form. Worth keeping safe in the placings.
